"v. 弄乱(头发) 【英】 v.弄乱(头发) (dishevel, rumple) 【记】 来自touse(吵闹，弄 乱)+le v. 弄乱(头发) = dishevel; 弄皱 【记】源于: touse(n 吵闹; v 弄乱)读: 唐僧, 见到唐僧这么啰嗦的人要挠头－弄乱头发 【记】音：头扫，打扫头，将头发弄乱；音：头搜，头上搜白头发会将头发弄乱；音：跳蚤，头发及身上有了跳蚤会将头发衣服搞乱 【相关】tussle 格斗,争斗 tousle (v.)  ""pull roughly, disorder, dishevel,"" mid-15c., frequentative of -tousen ""handle or push about roughly,"" probably from an unrecorded Old English *tusian, from Proto-Germanic *tus- (cognates: Frisian tusen, Old High German erzusen, German zausen ""to tug, pull, dishevel""); related to tease (v.). Related: Tousled; tousling."
